---
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="projects"
  description="Open-source projects by Tien Du."
>
  <div class="projects">
    <p class="projects-intro">
      Small tools for Linux operations, dependency analysis, bioinformatics,
      automation, and developer workflows.
    </p>
    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu/runwatch"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          RunWatch
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p class="tech">
        Python · Linux · systemd · cgroups · OpenMetrics
      </p>
      <p>
        A lightweight Linux service and process monitor built for operational
        visibility without requiring a full observability stack.
      </p>
      <p>
        RunWatch tracks process trees, CPU, memory, disk I/O, file descriptors,
        TCP/UDP connections, Unix sockets, and HTTP health checks. It supports
        structured JSON logs, OpenMetrics-compatible output, strict TOML
        configuration, atomic writes, and persistent monitoring through systemd.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu/depviz"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          depviz
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p class="tech">
        Python · PyPI · Conda · Bioconda · Graph Analysis · CLI · Caching
      </p>
      <p>
        A dependency-risk and upgrade-impact inspector for PyPI and
        Conda/Bioconda environments.
      </p>
      <p>
        depviz resolves package graphs, calculates dependency blast radius and
        transitive weight, explains why packages are present, estimates upgrade
        impact, renders ASCII dependency trees, identifies environment
        conflicts, and caches repeatable analysis results.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu/seqgrep"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          seqgrep
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p class="tech">
        Python · Bioinformatics · FASTA · FASTQ · Gzip · IUPAC · CLI · Multiprocessing
      </p>
      <p>
        A DNA-aware, grep-style search tool for biological sequences.
      </p>
      <p>
        seqgrep supports literal sequence search by default, optional IUPAC
        ambiguity matching, reverse-complement search, circular DNA boundary
        matches, FASTA/FASTQ input, gzip-compressed files, and chunked
        multiprocessing for long sequences.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu/gommitizen"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Gommitizen
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p class="tech">
        Go · CLI · Git · Conventional Commits
      </p>
      <p>
        A Go implementation of Commitizen for generating consistent
        conventional commit messages and supporting cleaner release workflows.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu/gentr"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          gentr
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p class="tech">
        Go · File Watching · Command Execution · CLI · Developer Tooling
      </p>
      <p>
        A lightweight command runner that watches files and directories for
        changes, then reruns a command automatically.
      </p>
      <p>
        gentr supports recursive watching, glob and stdin-based input,
        configurable output, and simple install and uninstall commands.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</PageLayout>